# =============================================================
# Edge Functions — environment
#
# IMPORTANT: SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_ANON_KEY and
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY are RESERVED secret names. The
# Supabase platform injects all three into every deployed
# function automatically — you do NOT set them, and the CLI
# will REJECT them if you try (`supabase secrets set` / a
# function .env that starts with SUPABASE_ fails to deploy).
#
# This file exists ONLY for fully-local runs via:
#     supabase start
#     supabase functions serve --env-file ./supabase/functions/.env.example
# where there is no platform to inject them.
#
# For local dev, `supabase start` prints these values, or copy
# them from: Dashboard → Project Settings → API.
#
# Do NOT commit a real .env — copy this to .env and fill it in.
# =============================================================

# --- Local-serve only (auto-injected when deployed) ---
SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-local-anon-key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-local-service-role-key

# --- Add any of YOUR OWN custom secrets below (these are the
#     only kind you would ever `supabase secrets set`). None are
#     required by the current 4 functions. Example:
# RYDER_API_KEY=
